---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy - VivaSpot">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-container">
      <span class="hero-tag">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Effective: December 23, 2024</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="content-container">
      <div class="legal-content">
        
        <p class="intro">iValu8, Inc. (dba "VivaSpot," "we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our websites, applications, WiFi services, and related products and services (collectively, the "Services").</p>

        <p>By using our Services, you consent to the data practices described in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, please do not use our Services.</p>

        <div class="highlight-box">
          <strong>Summary of Key Points:</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>We collect personal information when you use our WiFi services, including email addresses and phone numbers</li>
            <li>We use this information for marketing purposes, including email and SMS marketing</li>
            <li>We may share your information with our business partners and marketing affiliates</li>
            <li>You can opt-out of marketing communications at any time</li>
            <li>We retain your data as described in our data retention section</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
        <p><strong>Company:</strong> iValu8, Inc. (dba VivaSpot)<br>
        <strong>Address:</strong> PO Box 16111, Chapel Hill, NC 27514<br>
        <strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://vivaspot.com">https://vivaspot.com</a><br>
        <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@vivaspot.com">privacy@vivaspot.com</a></p>
        
        <p>VivaSpot provides WiFi marketing and automation services to businesses ("Subscribers"). When you connect to WiFi at a business using our Services, or interact with our websites and applications, this Privacy Policy applies to you.</p>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        
        <h3>2.1 Information You Provide Directly</h3>
        <p>We collect information you voluntarily provide when using our Services, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Name, email address, phone number, mailing address</li>
          <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Username, password, business name (for Subscribers)</li>
          <li><strong>WiFi Login Information:</strong> Email address, phone number, or social media login credentials used to access WiFi through our captive portals</li>
          <li><strong>Communications:</strong> Information you provide when contacting us, including customer service inquiries and feedback</li>
          <li><strong>Survey and Promotion Responses:</strong> Information submitted through surveys, contests, or promotional offers</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
        <p>When you use our Services, we automatically collect certain information, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Device type, operating system, unique device identifiers, MAC address, browser type and version</li>
          <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> General location based on IP address; precise location if you enable location services</li>
          <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, time spent on pages, links clicked, WiFi connection times and duration</li>
          <li><strong>Log Data:</strong> IP address, access times, referring URLs, error logs</li>
          <li><strong>Cookies and Tracking Technologies:</strong> Information collected through cookies, web beacons, and similar technologies (see Section 7)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.3 Information from Third Parties</h3>
        <p>We may receive information about you from third parties, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Social media platforms (if you log in using social media credentials)</li>
          <li>Business partners and marketing affiliates</li>
          <li>Data enrichment providers</li>
          <li>Analytics providers</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect for various purposes, including:</p>
        
        <h3>3.1 Providing and Improving Services</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Facilitating WiFi access at Subscriber locations</li>
          <li>Managing your account and providing customer support</li>
          <li>Processing transactions and sending related information</li>
          <li>Improving and developing our Services</li>
          <li>Analyzing usage patterns and trends</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 Marketing and Communications</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Sending promotional emails, newsletters, and offers from VivaSpot</li>
          <li>Sending promotional emails, newsletters, and offers from our Subscribers (the businesses where you access WiFi)</li>
          <li>Sending SMS/text messages with marketing communications, offers, and promotions</li>
          <li>Sharing your information with third-party marketing partners for targeted advertising</li>
          <li>Personalizing content and advertisements</li>
          <li>Conducting market research and analytics</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.3 Legal and Security Purposes</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Complying with legal obligations</li>
          <li>Enforcing our Terms of Use and other agreements</li>
          <li>Protecting our rights, privacy, safety, or property</li>
          <li>Detecting and preventing fraud or other illegal activities</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. How We Share Your Information</h2>
        <p>We may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>

        <h3>4.1 With Subscribers</h3>
        <p>When you connect to WiFi at a business using our Services, we share your information with that Subscriber so they can communicate with you about their products, services, and promotions.</p>

        <h3>4.2 With Marketing Partners</h3>
        <p>We may share your information with third-party marketing partners, advertisers, and affiliates for marketing and advertising purposes. This includes sharing email addresses, phone numbers, and other contact information for targeted marketing campaigns.</p>

        <h3>4.3 With Service Providers</h3>
        <p>We share information with vendors and service providers who perform services on our behalf, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email and SMS marketing platforms</li>
          <li>Cloud hosting and data storage providers</li>
          <li>Analytics and data processing services</li>
          <li>Payment processors</li>
          <li>Customer support services</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.4 Business Transfers</h3>
        <p>If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, financing, reorganization, bankruptcy, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.</p>

        <h3>4.5 Legal Requirements</h3>
        <p>We may disclose your information if required by law, regulation, legal process, or governmental request, or when we believe disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, your safety, or the safety of others.</p>

        <h3>4.6 With Your Consent</h3>
        <p>We may share your information for other purposes with your consent or at your direction.</p>

        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Retained indefinitely for marketing purposes unless you opt out</li>
          <li><strong>WiFi Usage Data:</strong> Retained for up to 7 years for analytics and compliance purposes</li>
          <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Retained for the duration of your account plus 7 years</li>
          <li><strong>Transaction Records:</strong> Retained as required by applicable law (typically 7 years)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Even after you opt out of marketing communications, we may retain your information for legal, security, and operational purposes.</p>

        <h2>6. Your Rights and Choices</h2>

        <h3>6.1 Marketing Opt-Out</h3>
        <p>You can opt out of marketing communications:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> Click the "unsubscribe" link at the bottom of any marketing email</li>
          <li><strong>SMS:</strong> Reply "STOP" to any text message</li>
          <li><strong>Contact Us:</strong> Email <a href="mailto:privacy@vivaspot.com">privacy@vivaspot.com</a> with your request</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Important:</strong> Opting out of communications from one Subscriber or campaign does not opt you out of all VivaSpot or partner communications. You may need to opt out separately from different senders.</p>

        <h3>6.2 Access and Correction</h3>
        <p>You may request access to your personal information or request corrections by contacting us at <a href="mailto:privacy@vivaspot.com">privacy@vivaspot.com</a>.</p>

        <h3>6.3 Data Deletion</h3>
        <p>You may request deletion of your personal information by contacting us. Please note that we may retain certain information as required by law or for legitimate business purposes, and deletion from our systems does not guarantee deletion from Subscriber or third-party systems.</p>

        <h3>6.4 Do Not Track</h3>
        <p>Our Services do not currently respond to "Do Not Track" browser signals. However, you can manage cookies and tracking through your browser settings.</p>

        <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
        <p>We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to collect and store information about your interactions with our Services.</p>

        <h3>7.1 Types of Cookies We Use</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> Required for the operation of our Services</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> Help us understand how visitors interact with our Services</li>
          <li><strong>Marketing Cookies:</strong> Used to deliver relevant advertisements and track campaign effectiveness</li>
          <li><strong>Preference Cookies:</strong> Remember your settings and preferences</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.2 Managing Cookies</h3>
        <p>You can manage cookies through your browser settings. Please note that disabling cookies may affect the functionality of our Services.</p>

        <h3>7.3 Third-Party Analytics</h3>
        <p>We use third-party analytics services, including Google Analytics, to help analyze how users interact with our Services. These services may use cookies and similar technologies to collect information about your use of our Services.</p>

        <h2>8. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Encryption of data in transit and at rest</li>
          <li>Access controls and authentication measures</li>
          <li>Regular security assessments and monitoring</li>
          <li>Employee training on data protection</li>
        </ul>
        <p>However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

        <h2>9. Data Breach Procedures</h2>
        <p>In the event of a data breach that affects your personal information, we will:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Investigate the breach and take steps to contain it</li>
          <li>Assess the risk to affected individuals</li>
          <li>Notify affected individuals and relevant authorities as required by applicable law</li>
          <li>Take measures to prevent future breaches</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence, including the United States. These countries may have different data protection laws. By using our Services, you consent to the transfer of your information to the United States and other countries.</p>

        <h2>11. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>Our Services are not intended for children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete that information. If you believe we have collected information from a child under 13, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@vivaspot.com">privacy@vivaspot.com</a>.</p>

        <h2>12. California Privacy Rights (CCPA)</h2>
        <p>If you are a California resident, you have additional rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA):</p>

        <h3>12.1 Right to Know</h3>
        <p>You have the right to request information about the categories and specific pieces of personal information we have collected about you, the categories of sources from which we collected the information, our business purposes for collecting the information, and the categories of third parties with whom we share the information.</p>

        <h3>12.2 Right to Delete</h3>
        <p>You have the right to request deletion of your personal information, subject to certain exceptions.</p>

        <h3>12.3 Right to Opt-Out of Sale</h3>
        <p>You have the right to opt out of the "sale" of your personal information. Under the CCPA, sharing personal information with third parties for marketing purposes may constitute a "sale." To opt out, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@vivaspot.com">privacy@vivaspot.com</a> or call 1-855-383-4662.</p>

        <h3>12.4 Right to Non-Discrimination</h3>
        <p>We will not discriminate against you for exercising your CCPA rights.</p>

        <h3>12.5 Categories of Information Collected and Shared</h3>
        <p>In the past 12 months, we have collected and may have shared for business purposes the following categories of personal information:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Identifiers (name, email, phone number, IP address, device identifiers)</li>
          <li>Internet or network activity (browsing history, WiFi usage)</li>
          <li>Geolocation data</li>
          <li>Commercial information (transaction history)</li>
          <li>Inferences drawn from the above</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>12.6 Submitting CCPA Requests</h3>
        <p>To submit a CCPA request, contact us at:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@vivaspot.com">privacy@vivaspot.com</a></li>
          <li>Phone: 1-855-383-4662</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We will verify your identity before processing your request.</p>

        <h2>13. European Privacy Rights (GDPR)</h2>
        <p>If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), United Kingdom, or Switzerland, you have additional rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR):</p>

        <h3>13.1 Legal Basis for Processing</h3>
        <p>We process your personal information based on:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Consent:</strong> When you provide consent for specific processing activities</li>
          <li><strong>Contract:</strong> When processing is necessary to fulfill our contractual obligations</li>
          <li><strong>Legitimate Interests:</strong> When processing is necessary for our legitimate business interests</li>
          <li><strong>Legal Obligation:</strong> When processing is required by law</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>13.2 Your GDPR Rights</h3>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access your personal information</li>
          <li>Rectify inaccurate personal information</li>
          <li>Request erasure of your personal information</li>
          <li>Restrict processing of your personal information</li>
          <li>Data portability</li>
          <li>Object to processing</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent at any time</li>
          <li>Lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>13.3 Contact for GDPR Inquiries</h3>
        <p>For GDPR-related inquiries, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@vivaspot.com">privacy@vivaspot.com</a>.</p>

        <h2>14. Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
        <p>Our Services may contain links to third-party websites and services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.</p>

        <h2>15. WiFi Services Specific Provisions</h2>
        <p>When you connect to WiFi through our Services:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>You consent to the collection of your contact information (email and/or phone number) for marketing purposes</li>
          <li>You consent to receive marketing communications from the business providing WiFi and from VivaSpot</li>
          <li>Your WiFi usage data may be collected and analyzed</li>
          <li>WiFi services are not inherently secure; we do not guarantee the security of data transmitted over WiFi</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>16. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The updated version will be indicated by an updated "Effective" date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically. Your continued use of our Services after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.</p>

        <h2>17. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:</p>
        
        <div class="contact-info">
          <p><strong>iValu8, Inc. (dba VivaSpot)</strong><br>
          112 Silo Drive, Suite 100<br>
          Chapel Hill, NC 27514</p>
          <p><strong>Privacy Inquiries:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@vivaspot.com">privacy@vivaspot.com</a><br>
          <strong>General Support:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@vivaspot.com">support@vivaspot.com</a><br>
          <strong>Phone:</strong> 1-855-383-4662<br>
          <strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://vivaspot.com">vivaspot.com</a></p>
        </div>

        <p class="last-updated"><em>Last Updated: December 23, 2024</em></p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    padding: 5rem 2rem 3rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--cream) 0%, #fff 50%, var(--cream-dark) 100%);
  }

  .hero-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--orange-500);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--charcoal-light);
  }

  /* Content Section */
  .content-section {
    background: white;
    padding: 3rem 2rem 5rem;
  }

  .content-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-content {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  .legal-content .intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--charcoal-light);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--cream-dark);
  }

  .legal-content h2:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-content h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--charcoal);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .legal-content li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content a {
    color: var(--orange-500);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .legal-content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .highlight-box {
    background: #fff3e0;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--orange-500);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
  }

  .highlight-box ul {
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .highlight-box li {
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .contact-info {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .contact-info p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .contact-info p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .last-updated {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--charcoal-light);
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 3rem 1.5rem 2rem;
    }

    .content-section {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem 3rem;
    }

    .legal-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
